        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:24PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Windham, or 9 miles south of Owego, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Campville, Nichols, Apalachin, Chenango Valley State Park, Conklin,
Tioga Terrace, Endicott, Windham, West Warren, and Windsor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
